e creation of these animals on the fifth day to inhabit the land and water separated on the third day is a symbol of the Resurrection of Christ.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aCreationvSermons. 0aSermons, SyriacvTranslations in to English. 0aSermons, Syriac. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh1 aEdward G., Mathews Jr., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishz978311061074108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2019z9783110606508oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066151440uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324118640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463241186423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463241186/original  a978-3-11-061074-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066151-4  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019